[[HarperCollins]] hired Scottish crime writer [[Val McDermid]] in 2012 to adapt ''Northanger Abbey'' for a modern audience, as a suspenseful teen thriller, the second rewrite in The Austen Project.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://newscorp.com/2013/10/09/harpercollins-announces-new-fiction-imprint-the-borough-press/ |title=HarperCollins Announces New Fiction Imprint: The Borough Press |date=9 October 2013 |newspaper=News Corp |access-date=8 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2012/jul/19/jane-austen-northanger-abbey-val-mcdermid |title=Jane Austen's Northanger Abbey to be reworked by Val McDermid |newspaper=The Guardian |last=Flood |first=Alison |date=19 July 2012 |access-date=4 August 2012}}</ref> McDermid said of the project, "At its heart it‚Äôs a teen novel, and a satire ‚Äì that‚Äôs something which fits really well with contemporary fiction. And you can really feel a shiver of fear moving through it. I will be keeping the suspense ‚Äì I know how to keep the reader on the edge of their seat. I think Jane Austen builds suspense well in a couple of places, but she squanders it, and she gets to the endgame too quickly. So I will be working on those things." The novel was published in 2014.<ref name=Baker2016>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/06/15/books/review/val-mcdermids-northanger-abbey.html |title=It Was a Dark and Stormy Night: Val McDermid's 'Northanger Abbey' |last=Baker |first=Jo |newspaper=New York Times |date=13 June 2014 |access-date=8 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=McDermid |first=Val |author-link=Val McDermid |title=Northanger Abbey |url=https://archive.org/details/northangerabbey0000mcde_g1m5 |url-access=registration |publisher=The Borough Press |year=2014 |isbn=978-0007504244}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/reviews/northanger-abbey-by-val-mcdermid-book-review-a-dark-daring-adaptation-complete-with-social-media-and-9203756.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220621/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/reviews/northanger-abbey-by-val-mcdermid-book-review-a-dark-daring-adaptation-complete-with-social-media-and-9203756.html |archive-date=21 June 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Northanger Abbey by Val McDermid, book review: A dark, daring adaptation - complete with social media and vampires |last=Forshaw |first=Barry |date=20 March 2014 |newspaper=The Independent |access-date=7 September 2016}}</ref>

